headline: HOOD Q2 Deep Dive: Product Expansion and Crypto Strategy Drive Results Amid Market Skepticism
summary: Financial services company Robinhood (NASDAQ:HOOD) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 45% year on year to $989 million. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.50 per share was 41.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
